  "overview" : "## Return Value\n\nHint of media's contents.\n\n## Overview\n\nAsk the media object for a hint of its contents. The hint is set at the time of the object's creation, should the creator have a clue as to what it may contain. The hint string does not change for the lifetime of the object and is also formed in the likeness of Apple's \"Apple_HFS\" strings or in the likeness of a UUID.",
  "rawMarkdown" : "---\nsource: https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/kernel\/iomedia\/1813522-getcontenthint\ncrawled: 2025-12-11T21:30:54Z\n---\n\n# getContentHint\n\n## Declaration\n\n```swift\nvirtual const char * getContentHint() const; \n```\n\n## Return Value\n\nHint of media's contents.\n\n## Overview\n\nAsk the media object for a hint of its contents. The hint is set at the time of the object's creation, should the creator have a clue as to what it may contain. The hint string does not change for the lifetime of the object and is also formed in the likeness of Apple's \"Apple_HFS\" strings or in the likeness of a UUID.\n\n## Miscellaneous\n\n- **copyPhysicalExtent**\n- **getAttributes**\n- **getBase**\n- **getContent**\n- **getPreferredBlockSize**\n- **getSize**\n- **handleClose**\n- **handleIsOpen**\n- **handleOpen**\n- **init**\n- **isEjectable**\n- **isFormatted**\n- **isWhole**\n- **isWritable**\n- **lockPhysicalExtents**\n- **read**\n- **synchronizeCache**\n- **unlockPhysicalExtents**\n- **unmap**\n- **write**\n\n",
